    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2004-04-22</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2004-07-13T19:07:53Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Idling Reduction Tax Credit Act of 2004 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a business tax credit for 50 percent of the cost of a qualifying idling reduction device, up to $3,500. Defines &quot;qualifying idling reduction device&quot; as any device that is: (1) installed on a heavy-duty diesel-powered on-highway vehicle to provide services that would otherwise require the operation of the main drive engine while the vehicle is temporarily parked or stationary; and (2) certified by the Secretary of Energy to reduce long-duration idling. Directs the Secretary to publish standards for certifying such devices.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
